On 28th, it was found that the Mie Prefectural Board of Education decided to remove the gender field of the prefectural high school entrance application for consideration of sexual minorities such as transgenders whose mental and physical properties do not match.
The Board of Education of the prefecture approved the entrance examination for students in FY18 by selecting gender fields and writing expressions, but the items themselves were eliminated from FY20.
For classification of classes and grouping of physical education, we use research papers created by junior high school.
However, in order to be able to freely fill in the questionnaire according to the circumstances of the student, the gender field that was selected is described.
According to the Board of Education, the gender section of the public high vows has been removed from Osaka Prefecture and Fukuoka Prefecture since FY19, and Hokkaido and Kanagawa Prefecture have decided to remove them from FY20.
