The Minister of Agriculture and Forestry of Nepal, Mie - Ise Shimbun
[In a recycling park in Toba City, a group of Nepalese Minister of Agriculture, Forestry and Forestry (right edge) and others visited recycling facilities.]
【Toba】 10 Nepalese Minister of Agriculture and Forestry Dawa Dolce Lama visited Toba City Hall in Mie Prefecture and the recycling park in Daimeito Town in the same city on the 26th to observe the composting technology of raw garbage.
In the country, most of the waste used to be disposed of in landfills, but with the introduction of the composting technology of garbage, which is being studied by Mr. Rio Hashimoto (67), a lecturer at the Japan Agricultural Management University in Tsu City through international students, the city of Timi, Kathmandu, started its efforts to introduce waste recycling into a model city to promote organic farming without pesticides.
