Aso, the express train of National Railways, is a temporary train, Hiroshima-Kumamoto, a 10-hour trip | Shizuoka Shimbun at Es
To wait for departure at JR Hiroshima Station, a temporary train with the image of the express train "Aso" of the JNR era = 28
People who enjoy a special train trip inspired by the express 'Aso' of the JNR era
A special train was operated between Hiroshima and Kumamoto on the 28th with the image of the express 'Aso' during the JNR era.
On the morning of the same day, about 240 people, including railway fans, boarded a blue 12-car train from Hiroshima Station and departed for Kumamoto Station for about 10 hours.
Aso was a night train that connected Kumamoto and Tokyo between 1950 and 1980.
The tour was limited to one round trip (two days) and was organized by Japanese travel as part of the "Kumamoto Destination Campaign" by JR companies.
The trains are made up of seven cars, including passenger cars and locomotives, and run on the Sanyo, Chikuho and Kagoshima lines.
A special headmark was drawn on Mt. Aso.
