Candir Barochi, who gained fame with photos posted on social media, was strangled in July 2016.
His brother, Kandir Baroch, a popular social media player in Pakistan, was convicted on Friday for his sister's murder and sentenced to life imprisonment with the most popular "honorary murder" in Pakistan.
He was strangled in July 2016 by Balochi, who was famous for his selfie photography - not as big as Western standards, but was provocative in Pakistan, where women were very strong.
His older brother, Muhammad, was arrested.
His brother said in a press conference a few days later that he had killed his sister, "Of course," and that his sister's actions were "not allowed" and that he did not regret what he did.
