The Yamagata Shimbun will donate 1,600 sheets of aluminum relief and heat shield for refugees and 5 outdoor storage boxes (equivalent to about 1 million yen) to four autonomous associations in the Atami area of Tsuruoka City, which were affected by the earthquake in June, which was the epicenter off the coast of the prefecture.
