[Okinaga Ryobu Sokyoku] The NPO ASA Amami Sports Academy (President Akira Sonoda and Amami City) and the Okinaga Ryobu Sports Club ELOVE (President Junya Maeda and Chinamachi) signed a partnership for the promotion of remote island sports on February 25.
In addition to actively cooperating in projects conducted by both organizations, such as training guidance for various competitions, we will also establish a mutual support system in terms of health management and prevention of injuries, such as when children from remote islands travel outside the island.
Both organizations mediate, send and share information about their trainers and instructors when training related to sports.
When the remote island team is traveling outside the island, they will work to solve problems such as the difficulty of the trainer in terms of travel expenses.
Specifically, in cooperation with the Kagoshima Sports Promotion Center, a general incorporated association of Kagoshima Prefecture, which is affiliated with the ASA, during tournaments on the mainland, such as prefectural tournaments, support is provided to prevent the performance of the players from falling due to fatigue during boat trips and consecutive nights.
In addition, during the tournament on Amami Oshima and Okinagarabe Island, it is said that it will support players who come from outside the island by cooperating with local orthopedic hospitals and hospitals.
On the 25th, the signing ceremony was held at Elabko in Chimei-cho, and President Sonoda and Maeda shook hands.
After that, both organizations co-hosted a training session with Athletic Trainer Yuichiro Hidaka.
Local sports boys and club leaders and parents learned how to use taping properly and how to prevent injuries.
