The Sonnet Media Networks (SMN) began advertising for header binding by "Prebid.js" in LFP.
LFP is a service that enables customers to purchase and plan their own advertising frameworks according to their needs.
The Service provides an effective advertising framework through DSP through collaboration with media companies.
Header biding is a mechanism that allows media companies to prioritize ads with high unit price by conducting fair bidding competition with multiple bidders.
It has been introduced mainly by major media as a solution that is transparent to media companies and is expected to improve profitability.
In the past, SSP has been providing advertising frames through SSP.
In recent years, in order to respond to requests from advertisers to deliver to specific advertising frames that have high affinity with individual commercial materials and brand images, LFP began in December last year, in collaboration with media companies, to directly purchase advertising frames to meet the needs of advertisers.
In response to header binding, the introduction of LFP will be expanded.
As a benefit for advertisers, LFP header binding allows them to participate in bidding directly for header binding target ad frames, and it is expected to improve their advertising delivery opportunities.
In addition, because the target media company is limited, the advertisement frame of the distribution company according to individual commercial materials and brand image is secured, preventing damage to brand value.
One of the advantages of media companies is that LFP's "wrapper solution," a solution that bundles and manages the code of each Vidder company, can be implemented in accordance with the wishes of media companies.
