【Students who promote fish nuggets and Thai cooked rice】At Owashi High School in Furuno-cho, Owashi City
[Owashi] Four third-year students from the Department of Information Business at Owashi High School in Furutono-cho, Owashi City, Mie Prefecture developed fish nuggets and Thai cooked rice using locally fried fish.
It was sold at the school's cultural festival on August 26.
This project is part of the high-level collaboration project of the Higashi Kishu Satellite, Mie University, which aims to revitalize the water industry and forestry industries, which are local industries in the Tokishu region.
The newly developed products include fish nuggets made from motttled meat caught in the Kumano Nada and rice cooked using aquaculture die from Owashi.
He said he was targeting young people.
Fish nuggets developed three types of fish nuggets, including tofu and gas shrimp from Owashi.
In cooperation with Kumano Fishing Co., Ltd., it is worn at the processing site of Yugi-cho, Kumano City.
Thai cooked rice is mixed with shiitake mushrooms and carrots.
"Odeo fish Ichibaoto" (Kotono-cho, the same city) is directly managed by the fishery company "Owashi monozukuri" in Hayashi-cho, Owashi City.
Classes began in June.
They visited the Owashi factory and deepened their understanding of the water industry.
The workshop discussed consumer needs and tried prototypes.
He also invented naggets using aji, but he adopted mutts because of the smell peculiar to fish.
Masaki Yamaguchi (17) said, "It's a product that can be eaten by people who are not good at fish, and I'm glad that many people can eat it."
It is said that they are negotiating with tourist facilities in the city to sell goods.
