The 300-year history of kumi Odori / Education Promotion Project | Miyako Mainichi Shimbun Website - The latest news on Miyako Island is packed!
Workshops in Kagamihara
Workshop on the role and effect of five musical instruments played by kumi odori was introduced on February 26.
A group dance workshop (hosted by the Prefectural Board of Education and Education Agency) was held at Kagamihara Junior High School on the 26th.
All students attended and learned about the 300-year history and birth of kumidori, as well as the acoustic effects and use of musical instruments played.
At the workshop, members of the OB Association of the Ryukyu Performing Arts Department of the Prefectural University of Arts introduced the role of each instrument in kumidori while playing sanshin, koto, taiko, kokyu and flute.
The host was Mr. Kawamata of the OB association from Miyakojima City and introduced the charm of kumi odori.
In this workshop, I learned about the three components of kumi odori (music, chant, Ryukyu dance) and how five types of musical instruments are represented in dance.
As for the sanshin, it was explained that it was an element of the movement and emotion of the characters along with the songs, and that Kokyu was pulling up the songs and the melody of the sanshin while playing.
In the latter half, the students experienced the sound of the instruments and felt the appeal of the instruments.
The purpose of this initiative is to get familiar with "Ryukyu classical music" through musical instruments and to get interested in "gumi Odori" by many students.This is the first time in Miyako.
