9.2% of high school students in Taiwan "experienced" rate increase that does not contraception = Health Authorities Survey (Central Focus Taiwan) - Yahoo!
(Taipei 27) The National Health Bureau of the Ministry of Health and Welfare (Ministry of Health) announced on September 26 a survey on sexual intercourse among high school students in Taiwan.
According to this, 9.2% of students answered that they had experience.
It was revealed that about five of them did not have contraception.
The survey was conducted in 2017 for students enrolled in high schools, specialized high schools, and vocational schools.
Compared to the previous survey in 2015, the percentage of students with sexual intercourse experience decreased slightly from 11.1%.
On the other hand, 22.6% of men and women aged 15 to 17 answered that they did not contraception due to the latest sexual activity, exceeding 19.2% in the previous year.
The breakdown is 28.8% of males (22.6%) and 12.2% of females (14.5 percent).
The station pointed out that modern youths have more opportunities to obtain information on the Internet, and their thinking is likely to be biased by misinformation.
It is called to have the right knowledge to neglect contraception and increase the risk of pregnancy as well as infection.
