JR Omura Line, which saw operation due to damage from the track due to Typhoon No. 17, resumed operation from the start of the 27th morning.
The JR Omura Line, the Sasebo Line, and the Nagasaki Main Line started in the morning of the 27th and returned to normal operation.
The JR Omura Line is the intermediate point between Kawabata Station and Heki Station, and the protective shores along the tracks collapsed due to the typhoon, and the foundations flowed.
The number of JR trains in Nagasaki Prefecture decreased and the number of trains continued to deteriorate.
According to the JR Kyushu Nagasaki Branch, the restoration work on the 26th was completed, and the operation resumed after the trial operation train ran early on the 27th.
