Although I had a boyfriend all the time, I had a long distance romance due to his work ...
I was told to marry someday, but I couldn't see the goal.
In such a situation, how can we connect the situation to marriage by side?
Editorial I of Nikkei Doors asked Professor Tomoyoshi Morikawa to give a lecture on "love science" at Waseda University.
Prof. Morikawa's advice derived from detailed data analysis is mandatory.
what's this?
I am worried about whether I should continue dating my boyfriend during a long distance romance.
I want to continue living in Kansai where I work and my parents live, but his place is Tokyo.
Since it is a trading company, it is possible to transfer overseas.
It is said that we will marry in the future, but we cannot see the goal at all.
What should I do?
(23 years old, manufacturer, administrative office)
The couple who got married from long distance love is a minority.
Nikkei doors Editorial Department (hereinafter, -) C is in a distant relationship with her boyfriend for a year and a half.
There is also the word "to be tested in distance and the two become stronger."
Prof. Tomoyoshi Morikawa (hereinafter referred to as Morikawa) Speaking of distance love, the survey conducted by DeNA Travel (in August 2017, 1147 people answered) is famous.
Since love is done using five senses, the relationship is deepened by looking at the opponent (visual), listening to the voice (heart), connecting the hand (touch), smelling (or smelling), kissing (taste).
However, in the case of long distance love, there are many cases where you can hear the voice by phone.
It may be difficult to keep up with hearing alone.
There is also a cost problem.
If you go to your opponent's house, you will be burdened by the time and effort to move to the transportation cost, and your body is still a holiday to heal work fatigue.
I feel refreshed when I go home.
Is that the only way to break apart when it comes to distance?
Morikawa I think it will work if you are a couple who can endure without having to meet frequently or a couple who have a certain period of time in advance.
You'll be engaged a year later, or you'll come back from your transfer two years later.
It may be difficult if you do not see a future landing point.
