Isuzu's large truck Giga, the latest model to be released worldwide...Tokyo Motor Show 2019 (Response) - Yahoo!
Isuzu Motors will release the latest model of the heavy-duty truck "Giga" for the first time in the world at the Tokyo Motor Show 2019 held at Tokyo Big Sight from October 24 to November 4.
In addition to the latest advanced safety equipment, Isuzu's flagship model, Giga, has added new equipment to reduce fatigue to drivers.
It contributes to safe operation by pre-clash brakes that detect pedestrians and bicycles, blind spot monitors that support the suppression of winding accidents at right left turn and lane change, and variable light LED headlamps.
In addition, it contributes to reducing the fatigue of the driver by cruises between full-speed milliwaves and new high roof cabs that follow the preceding car at full speed.
In addition, vehicle operation and dynamic management systems have also expanded vehicle condition items.
New monitoring of the operation status of safety equipment and support safe operation.
The world premiere of FL-IR, which expresses future logistics networks as a show model.
FL-IR focuses on the ultrasonic conversation and behavioral habits seen in fish and other fishes, as well as the similarity between connected and column running.
The exterior incorporates a bio design that gives an efficient image of a robot with the motif of a shark, and features a style that contrasts the pre-filtered cab with an organic shape that breaks the wind and the rigid aero device covering it.
The interior features a layer design that replaces dashboards with manual and automatic driving mode changes.
The seat is placed in the center and combines comfortable operation and habitability.
The next generation of small delivery vehicles, the ElfEV Walkthrough van, will also be the first worldwide release.
In addition to zero emissions and low noise, we incorporate a walk-through structure that was realized only by EVs, and take into account the efficiency of the driver's working environment and the distribution work.
The driver's seat is equipped with a rotating seat to support driving inside the driver.
In terms of safety, it is equipped with a wide range of electronic mirror systems and a 3D surround multiview that can be seen all around the vehicle.
In addition, he will exhibit the Japan's first hybrid bus "Elga Duo" jointly developed by Hino, the small truck "Elf," which has undergone significant improvements, and the diesel 4JZ1 engine that realizes both the latest emission regulations and fuel efficiency.
In addition, a video and panel exhibition introduces the utilization support "PRISM" and initiatives for natural gas vehicles.
In Family Space, there are touch panels that can be seen in videos on how various trucks are used, and photo booths that can become truck drivers.
Arriving at an unmanned supply machine, Space Station Catching with a Robot Arm | Shizuoka Shimbun
Konotori No. 8, an unmanned supply vehicle that arrived at the International Space Station.
The robot arm of the station is growing from the bottom left (NASA provided).
The International Space Station (ISS) successfully caught Konotori 8 and applauded JAXA officials on 28th (JAXA provided)
The spacecraft Konotori 8 (JAXA) of the Japan Aerospace Exploration Agency (JAXA), which carries supplies to the International Space Station at an altitude of about 400 kilometers, arrived near the station on the night of 28th.
The spacecraft was launched 25 days from Tanegashima Space Center in Kagoshima Prefecture and gradually advanced through the control of JAXA Tsukuba Space Center.
Finally, flying at the same speed as the station eliminates the difference in speed and approaches to a distance of about 10 meters.
The robot arm, 17 and 6 meters long, grabs the supply machine.
The aircraft had about 5 to 3 tons of supplies.
After attaching it to the station, the airmen carry the luggage.
